# Changelog

All notable changes to this project will be documented here.

The format follows [Keep a Changelog](https://keepachangelog.com/en/1.0.0/).

---

## [1.0.0] — Initial Release

### Added
- GUI desktop application built with Python `tkinter`
- Multi-file Excel import: load any number of monthly billing exports at once
- Automatic billing month detection from data column (`বিল মাস`) or filename
- Merge engine: consolidates all monthly files into one master DataFrame with one row per unique consumer
- Office-wise splitting: separates consumers into 10 sub-office Excel files based on the first 6 digits of their account number (`হিসাব নম্বর`)
- Low-usage filter: configurable threshold (default 150 kWh) — keeps only consumers who recorded usage at or below the threshold in any tracked month
- Formatted Excel output: colour-coded headers (dark blue / medium blue), alternating row fills, frozen panes at column C / row 3, auto column widths
- Missing monthly values filled with `0` (not blank) to ensure filter logic works correctly across all months
- Mobile number normalisation: strips decimals, prepends leading zero if 10 digits, marks missing as `N/A`
- Bengali month labels in output column headers (জানুয়ারি, ফেব্রুয়ারি, … ডিসেম্বর)
- Threaded processing — GUI remains responsive during long runs
- Colour-coded live log panel (green = success, red = error, yellow = warning, blue = info)
- Windows batch launchers: `Run_Merger.bat`, `Low_Consumption_Consumer_Tracker.bat`
- PyInstaller build script: `Build_EXE.bat` produces a standalone `Electricity Bill Merger.exe`
- Auto-installs `pandas` and `openpyxl` on first run if missing
- Output folder opens automatically in Windows Explorer on completion

### Offices supported
HQ, Daulotpur, Kumarkhali, Mirpur, Bheramara, Swastipur, Khoksha, Poradah, Pragpur, Panti
